{
  "stem": "27509.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When I came later to Melbourne and I had to start fighting for-- for the Jewish content of Mount Scopus College, I already had some inkling what Jewish education in [INAUDIBLE] is.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that is-- that was experience.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "What I saw at that-- at that ghetto was very, very depressing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What did you witness?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we-- we went-- after we inspected the school, we went to have a look at dormitories.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were people-- some people lived in homes, some people lived in dormitories.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was old warehouses converted totally, the entire area, into two-story bed setups.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, the middle of the day, we saw people lying on the beds with nothing to do.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some played cards, some-- it dispirited, without purpose, without hope, without-- without an inkling to what to do.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from what we saw and what we knew was that the higher the people were in their previous life socially, the more well off they were, the most-- the more well-provided they were economically, the further they fell in their new role as refugees.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because they were not prepared.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They never had to struggle for daily existence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The shock of that fall from grace, so to speak, in terms of their well-being, was so great that they could never find to-- to stand on their own feet again.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Those who didn't have and had to go and-- and make a living could care less.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They-- they-- they sold dollars, they sold pins, they sold needles, they sold shaving treatment.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Anything is sold because that was natural and normal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Those people who were doctors and lawyers and-- and-- and-- and the upper crust of society, they were completely lost.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
